<img width="750" height="422" class="wp-image-1573618" style="width: 600px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Fire.jpg" alt="Katsina House Assembly" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Fire.jpg?width=750&amp;auto_optimize=medium 750w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Fire-300x169.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Fire-58x33.jpg?width=58&amp;auto_optimize=medium 58w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Fire-260x146.jpg?width=260&amp;auto_optimize=medium 260w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Fire-200x113.jpg?width=200&amp;auto_optimize=medium 200w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" />By Marie-Therese NanlongA fire outbreak from a petrol-laden tanker that fell at the Polo roundabout in Jos, Plateau State has left one person dead while property worth millions of naira were destroyed.Among the property destroyed are parts of the Veterinary Teaching Hospital of the University of Jos, the Jos Metropolitan Development Board shopping complex, the Oando petrol station as well as some nearby makeshift shops.